headline: US bank sector sees profit dip due to Capital One-Discover deal: FDIC
summary: WASHINGTON (Reuters) -The completed merger between Capital One and Discover Financial weighed down bank profits in the second quarter, as the sector reported $69.9 billion in profits, down 1% from the quarter prior.  The Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation said accounting rules required the merged institution to set aside a relatively large amount of provision expense.  Bank profits were down $677.3 million for the quarter.
